================================================================================
LOAD GENERATION LESSONS LEARNED
================================================================================

❌ Method 1: Flask endpoint with intensity=2
   Result: 50% CPU (insufficient)
   Reason: 2 threads / 2 CPUs = 50% per CPU

❌ Method 2: Flask endpoint with intensity=4  
   Result: 50% CPU (capped by app code)
   Reason: App limited to 2×CPU count = 4 threads max

❌ Method 3: Flask endpoint with intensity=12 (after raising cap to 8x)
   Result: Still ~50% CPU
   Reason: Gunicorn worker process model limits parallel execution

✅ Method 4: Direct Python multiprocessing (8 processes)
   Command: python3 ~/direct_stress.py 8
   Result: 100% CPU sustained
   Reason: True parallel processes, not limited by web server workers

RECOMMENDATION: Use direct_stress.py for reliable CPU load testing

